		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.13]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=ctbrew&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;   OK I would think the question would best be answered on a normal non-PVP context, as in, which is better in a normal game setting?  (Unless you're on a PVP server).  I have a 55 magi and a 30 necro, and I can tell you right now the necro is a better soloer, because with fear kiting your pet doesn't have to be as tough- a mage is much more limited in what it can take on, too tough a mob will make a speedbump of the pet.  Of course too tough a mob will mean the necro won't be able to fear the mob either, but there seems to be more latitude there with the necro.  A mage's nukes just won't land on a really tough mob either, and I tend to think DOTs will land more readily on tough mobs. I can say my necro is a much more flexible character, at least at 30, he can fear, ghetto-mezz, give mana to others, heal a bit, all sorts of stuff.  I don't know what all a necro can do at higher levels, but at 30 my necro is more well-rounded than my mage was.<br />     BUT- and this may be just me- I find the necro to be MUCH harder to play.  I really gotta concentrate, especially if I'm fear kiting.  My main is a pally, and (believe it or not) he's much more difficult to play than a magician.  My magician is relaxing, /assist, send in the pet, malo, nuke.  Not hard.  I've never seen this mentioned in a mage vs. necro board, not sure if others find this to be true.  <br />     At higher levels everyone has their preferences.  I think I'd rather have a necro when going against really tough mobs, as in a raid setting, but in a exp grind group, probly a mage.  Kinda like the pally vs. warrior scenario, come to think of it. Anyway babbling now hope this helps. <br />     </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />"Cigarettes, souvenirs, party tricks...."</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
